race.comment: The lightly raced WHISKEY MISS (10) has returned in fine order this prep. Scored a big maiden win first-up at Lismore then drove hard late to finish third in a tight go over 1250m at Ballina. No issue with this step up in distance - just needs luck from a wide gate to be in the finish. LADY ALABAMA (7) looked to have every chance but just missed the placings behind MONTGOMERY over this course and distance last time out. Form prior to that was difficult to knock so she deserves another chance. SINATRA (6) was lining up for only the second time when he comfortably took out a maiden over today's journey at Lismore recently. Has more upside than his rivals and can win again. HYPOTHERMIA (9) just missed in a similar race here two back then struggled at the mile last start. Worth another chance back to a more suitable journey. GOLDEN COPPER (3) is racing well this prep and gets all the favours from her lovely draw.
